| project Severity = tostring(Details.severity), Time = todatetime(Details.startDateTime), State = tostring(Details.alertState)
| where Time {TimeRange:query}
| summarize NewAlerts=countif(State=="New"), AckAlerts=countif(State=="Acknowledged"), ClosedAlerts=countif(State=="Closed")

| extend ClosedAlerts_bottom=strcat("Closed: ", tostring(ClosedAlerts))

Confluence Link)

This measures the ratio of Committed Bytes to the Commit Limit—in other words, the amount of virtual memory in use. This indicates insufficient memory if the number is greater than 80 percent. The obvious solution for this is to add more memory

Recommendation: If Virtual Machines are consistenly above 80% each day then it is recommened that more memory is added to the Virtual Machine. Adding additional VMs to spread out the user load Or Increasing VM SKUs is recommended.

content.query:
Perf
| where ObjectName == 'Memory' 
| where CounterName == '% Committed Bytes In Use' 
| summarize AggregatedValue = avg(CounterValue) by Computer, bin(TimeGenerated, 15m), _ResourceId 
| where AggregatedValue > 80 
| extend resDetails = split(_ResourceId, '/') 
| project TimeGenerated, Computer, ['% Committed Bytes In Use'] = round(AggregatedValue, 2), subId = resDetails[2], ThresholdLimit='80'
| sort by TimeGenerated

| join kind=leftouter (

        | distinct Computer, Cpus, _ResourceId) on Computer, _ResourceId

| extend resDetails = split(_ResourceId, '/')

| where RealQueueLength >= 10
| sort by RealQueueLength
